{"name": "answer", "arguments": {"kg": "wikidata", "sparql": "SELECT ?country ?countryLabel (COUNT(DISTINCT ?headOfGov) AS ?count)
WHERE {
  ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256.
  ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46.
  ?country p:P35 ?statement.
  ?statement ps:P35 ?headOfGov.
  ?statement pq:P580 ?startDate.
  FILTER(?startDate >= "2009-01-01T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime)
  OPTIONAL { ?country rdfs:label ?countryLabel. FILTER(LANG(?countryLabel) = "en") }
}
GROUP BY ?country ?countryLabel
ORDER BY DESC(?count)", "answer": "The data shows European countries' heads of government (not strictly 'prime ministers' as title varies) since 2009. San Marino leads with 20 heads of government (due to their dual Captains Regent system), followed by Bosnia and Herzegovina (8), Kosovo (5), and Poland (5). Most countries had 1 head of government in this period (e.g., Belgium, Netherlands, Spain, Ireland, Cyprus)."}}

